 Lagos  The Nigeria Cycling Federation (NCF) said it has met with the  Federal Road Safety Commission to ensure the success of the series of events  to mark this year’s World Bicycle Day. The NCF disclosed that United Nations set aside every third day of June to mark the World Bicycle Day to increase the awareness of cycling. This year’s event is put together by FT Cycle Care to commemorate the bicycle day in Lagos. To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .